## Naming Anti-Patterns

### ❌ Avoid These

```ruby
# Bad: Abbreviations
usr = User.first           # Use: user
art = Article.find(1)      # Use: article
cat = Category.all         # Use: category/categories

# Bad: Single letter variables (except loops)
u = User.first             # Use: user
a = 5                      # Use: count, total, etc.

# Bad: Hungarian notation
strName = "John"           # Use: name
intCount = 5               # Use: count
boolActive = true          # Use: active

# Bad: Vague names
data = fetch_something()   # Use: articles, users, etc.
result = calculate()       # Use: total, sum, average, etc.
temp = x + y              # Use: total, sum, etc.

# Bad: Redundant names
user_user = User.first            # Just: user
article_model = Article.first     # Just: article
get_article = Article.find(1)     # Just: article
```
